  {
    "client_msg_id": "3f4d8bd6-b88f-414a-8b07-8e252121b9ff",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Had an interesting video call yesterday, about data management in large-scale distributed computations (think bioinformatics etc.). Someone with a lot of experience in both practice and teaching said that an important lesson is to keep most relevant metadata in filenames. Her experience is that metadata in the files (in the file formats that explicitly provide metadata fields) is often wrong in practice, because it's invisible. Users don't care to look at it (an extra step, not always obvious), and then tools don't update it, because, why update something that nobody looks at?\nSo the \"use text because it is so much more accessible\" principle holds even for the small text bites that are filenames.",
    "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
    "ts": "1637220473.095000",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "e169f54bbaf8",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2021-03-12/1859691333940_e169f54bbaf8b9b36b12_72.png",
      "first_name": "Konrad",
      "real_name": "Konrad Hinsen",
      "display_name": "Konrad Hinsen",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "konrad.hinsen",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "7oVf",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Had an interesting video call yesterday, about data management in large-scale distributed computations (think bioinformatics etc.). Someone with a lot of experience in both practice and teaching said that an important lesson is to keep most relevant metadata in filenames. Her experience is that metadata in the files (in the file formats that explicitly provide metadata fields) is often wrong in practice, because it's invisible. Users don't care to look at it (an extra step, not always obvious), and then tools don't update it, because, why update something that nobody looks at?\nSo the \"use text because it is so much more accessible\" principle holds even for the small text bites that are filenames."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
